{{Jews and Judaism sidebar}}
The '''Berman Jewish Policy Archive''' ('''BJPA'''), housed at the [https://ed.stanford.edu/ Graduate School of Education at Stanford University]<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.bjpa.org/Pages/index.cfm|title=About BJPA {{!}} Berman Jewish Policy Archive @ Stanford University|website=www.bjpa.org|access-date=2017-02-28}}</ref> is a centralized [[electronic database]] of [[American Jews|Jewish communal]] [[policy]] research.<ref>{{cite web |title=Searchable Trove of Documents |url=http://wagner.nyu.edu/centers/bjpa |publisher=[[New York University]] |accessdate=21 December 2013 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131224120122/http://wagner.nyu.edu/centers/bjpa |archivedate=24 December 2013 |df= }}</ref> Its collection contains more than 20,000 documents, with holdings spanning from 1900 until today. It also is connected to the [http://jewishquestions.bjpa.org/ Jewish Survey Question Bank], a freely available repository of survey tools and questionnaires. The BJPA partners with the [[North American Jewish Data Bank]]; together they source the largest publicly available collection of Jewish policy research. The BJPA was established through the [[Mandell L. and Madeleine H. Berman Foundation]], the [[Charles H. Revson Foundation]], and continued with support from the [https://jimjosephfoundation.org/ Jim Joseph Foundation].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.bjpa.org/Pages/index.cfm|title=About BJPA {{!}} Berman Jewish Policy Archive @ Stanford University|website=www.bjpa.org|access-date=2017-02-28}}</ref>
The director and founder is [[Steven M. Cohen]].<ref>{{cite web| title=Management, Graduate Student Assistants, and Alumni |url=http://www.bjpa.org/About/staff.cfm |publisher=[[New York University]] |accessdate=21 December 2013}}</ref>
The associate director is [https://ed.stanford.edu/faculty/aykelman Ari Y. Kelman]
